; Regression test for issue #2131
;
; When using market-value mode (-V) combined with period mode (-M/--period),
; price changes that occur in periods containing no real transactions must
; still generate revaluation postings in the output.
;
; Before the fix, output_revaluation() set xdata.date to the intermediate
; price date but did not update xdata.value_date.  Because get_value_date()
; checks xdata.value_date before falling back to date(), the market()
; expression in total_expr always evaluated against the period-end date
; (set by interval_posts) rather than the intermediate price date.  This
; caused every intermediate revaluation to produce a diff of zero, so the
; entries were silently dropped.
;
; The fix makes output_revaluation() temporarily override xdata.value_date
; alongside xdata.date, so that market(display_total, value_date, exchange)
; uses the correct revaluation date.

commodity ACME
    format 0 ACME

P 2022/07/01 ACME $100.00
P 2022/08/01 ACME $200.00

2022/07/01 Buy ACME
    Assets:Investments     1 ACME @ $100.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg -V -M -e 2022/09/01 Assets:Investments
22-Jul-01 - 22-Jul-31           Assets:Investments          $100.00      $100.00
22-Aug-01 Commodities revalued  <Revalued>                  $100.00      $200.00
end test
